THE MBTA’S OWN DATA indicate passenger traffic on the Green Line is declining, but agency officials say they don’t believe the numbers.

Jeffrey Gonneville, the T’s chief operating officer, told the Fiscal Management and Control Board on Monday that the Green Line is the nation’s busiest light rail line, providing more than 200,000 trips each weekday.
